    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cd8bce36_b7df833f",
        "filename": "starlark/starlarkprotov2/loader.go",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 62,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-08T21:52:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I thought more about this and decided to keep using atomic counter. The problem with pointers is that they can be \"reused\" if one object is gc\u0027ed and replaced with another. This may cause subtle bugs (I hit this kind of crap when using id(...) as map keys in python).\n\nIt is probably fine to use pointers, since supposedly .Hash() is used only when adding stuff to dict in Starlark, and dicts retain pointers to keys (so gc shouldn\u0027t collect live things, so address reuse shouldn\u0027t happen), but this  may be fragile in face of possible future changes.\n\nRemoved the comment about pointers.",
      "parentUuid": "27d16fd8_8bf5772e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 61,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 62,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "fe63567820986978d89e3c3f57c3a740c9cf802c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
