    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e77ada7b_90954738",
        "filename": "starlark/starlarkprotov2/message.go",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 195,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-08T21:52:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e can we?\n\nwe can, but I don\u0027t want to implement this now since no one is sharing Starlark values across goroutines. If they do, their own fault not reading the docs Message where it is state it\u0027s not safe.\n\n\u003e What about repeated message fields?\n\nThey can be initialized to a frozen empty list. Unlike Python, in Starlark all structures are freezable (it is part of base starlark.Value interface).\n\n\u003e Why is an internal lock insufficient?\n\nWhat lock?",
      "parentUuid": "822914de_da387e04",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 194,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 195,
