        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-08T19:08:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thinking about this... why not? The cost is linearly proportional to the input, which seems OK? I think this means we\u0027ll end up with bogus values, but not seeing where they were assigned. Couldn\u0027t we also simultaneously reduce the cost of ToProto by converting dicts to Messages too?\n\nI think this would also potentially make Attr cheaper because m.fields would always be string-\u003eMessage, string-\u003eRepeated(primitive) or string-\u003eRepeated(Message), right?\n\nLike if I have\n\n  message Foo {\n    repeated Message bar \u003d 1;\n  }\n\nAnd do\n\n  f \u003d Foo()\n  f.bar \u003d [10]\n  f.bar[0].field  \n\nwhat happens?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 243,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 243,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "fe63567820986978d89e3c3f57c3a740c9cf802c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
