      "message": "Discussed offline, not changing for now.\n\n\u003e Thinking about this... why not? The cost is linearly proportional to the input, which seems OK? I think this means we\u0027ll end up with bogus values, but not seeing where they were assigned. Couldn\u0027t we also simultaneously reduce the cost of ToProto by converting dicts to Messages too?\n\u003e \n\u003e I think this would also potentially make Attr cheaper because m.fields would always be string-\u003eMessage, string-\u003eRepeated(primitive) or string-\u003eRepeated(Message), right?\n\u003e \n\u003e Like if I have\n\u003e \n\u003e   message Foo {\n\u003e     repeated Message bar \u003d 1;\n\u003e   }\n\u003e \n\u003e And do\n\u003e \n\u003e   f \u003d Foo()\n\u003e   f.bar \u003d [10]\n\u003e   f.bar[0].field  \n\u003e \n\u003e what happens?\n\nAttribute access error trying to read \u0027field\u0027 from an int in `f.bar[0].field`.",
